# Non-Functional Requirements — {Agent Name}

## Default targets

Inherited from `projects/{p}/project.config.yaml nfr.*` unless overridden per feature.

| NFR | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| P95 response time | 2000 ms | Per `project.config.yaml nfr.responseTimeMsP95` |
| Availability | 99.5% | Per `project.config.yaml nfr.availability` |
| Error rate | < 0.5% | Per `project.config.yaml nfr.errorRate` |

## Platform-specific NFRs

If this platform has unique non-functional concerns (e.g., F&O batch throughput targets, integration latency by pattern, Power BI dataset size limits), document them here with their default targets and how they're measured.

## Override path

Per-feature NFRs can be declared in the feature's spec under §6 Non-Functional Requirements. The spec's NFRs override the project defaults for that feature.

## Verification

Each NFR target should be associated with a verification approach (load test, monitoring dashboard, run-book check). When the FDD is authored, §5.4 NFR Mapping per Feature links each functional requirement to its NFR targets.
